{
  "stem": "10162.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On the other hand, I just had this feeling that I have to do this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I was going back and forth, torturing myself between these two extremes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then I decided for the first time, I sought out a psychologist.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I went to her.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "By the way, she was a Christian woman, who was extremely helpful.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she said, tell me, and I will write it for you.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was going there maybe six, eight months before it-- we gave birth to an answer.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then finally, they had-- and then also this letter asked them, would you be willing eventually to come to a reunion which we are planning in a year or a year and a half or something, in this site?",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, in my mind, this site really didn't exist on this world-- in this world, you know?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so then to take a trip there?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So anyway, I went.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I went.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You were allowed to bring someone with you.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were paying your full fare for a week and half of your companion's.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I took my daughter.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And, I must say, I had these paranoid thoughts to myself on the plane, that probably they hijack the plane and they'll put us right back underground, and nobody will ever know what happened to us, and you know.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so I arrived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the whole town was getting ready for this for a long time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had-- with the German precision and planning, you know, the whole week, the festivities were planned.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then they were-- everything was kosher, by the way.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was huge buffets.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the-- and the local women were all baking and cooking and serving us and taking our coat and taking-- it really was kind of surreal.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they had lectures.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they had dignitaries.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they had German television and radio.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The main thing, of course, was to see each other for the first time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Nobody-- of course, nobody recognized anybody after 45 years.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It's a difference between being 15 or 60.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] But the most interesting and the greatest thing for me and for everybody else was that all this paranoia that we thought we were living with, that only I thought these things on the plane-- it turned out everybody thought that on the plane.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Only I had these feelings for 45 years that, should I say it or shouldn't I say it?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Or why is it that I go down to this German deli, which has been there forever, and I ask for-- I don't know-- cream cheese, and I look at this guy behind a counter, and I suddenly see him in a Nazi uniform in my mind.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So it turned out everybody-- everybody-- went through this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that was very cathartic right away, that I'm not crazy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So for a while, we were in some kind of school buildings-- building, where we had one-- one woman who was one of us, an older woman.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She must have been at least 30, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was like a mother figure.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we didn't like it there, me and my girlfriends, because it was like American soldiers came and went.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And some girls went with them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were kind of scared and didn't like this whole thing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then one day, this woman who took care of us said that there are a few American Red Cross ladies who came and wanted to know are there any girls who speak German and English.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she said, yes, as a matter of fact, there are a few who are nice girls.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she asked, why?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she said, well, because we are in this nearby, large airport base.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we would need somebody, a few people, who could translate or interpret for us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So she asked us, would you like to go?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And said, oh, yes, we would like to go.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So one, two, three, we got in the car with them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we went over to-- it was called Fritzlar, this airport where we went.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Fritzladen?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Fritzlar-- Fritzlar, F-R-I-T-Z-L-A-R.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And after that, we moved with the whole base to another airport base nearby.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I don't remember the name of that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so these women were very, very nice to us, the Red Cross ladies.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Her name was Betty Cushing, I remember.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the story was that we had a little room, like a little maid's room, but with two of us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it was very nice, two to a room, in the Red Cross building with the Rod Cross cafeteria.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we never, ever had to interpret anything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were-- we were baking donuts for the rest of our stay.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
